-- Brazilian Stock Movers: Embraer, Pao de Acucar, Vigor Alimentos
-- B y   D e n y s e   G o d o y
-- 2012-06-22T21:44:27Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-06-22/brazil-movers-column-abril-embraer-pao-de-acucar-and-vigor.html
The following companies had  unusual 
price changes in  Sao Paulo  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses, and prices are as of the market close. Preferred
shares are usually the most-traded class of stock.  The  Bovespa (IBOV)  Index rose 0.1 percent to 55,439.50.  Cia. Brasileira de Distribuicao Grupo Pao  de Acucar (PCAR4
BS) gained 2 percent to 75.00 reais. Billionaire Abilio Diniz is
handed control of  Brazil ’s biggest retailer to French group
 Casino Guichard-Perrachon SA (CO)  today. Casino plans to convert
preferred shares into common shares in order to list its stock
on the Bovespa’s Novo Mercado section, newspaper Folha de
S.Paulo reported, citing unidentified people close to the French
company. Casino denied the report, according to a press officer
who asked not to be identified in accordance with company
policy.  Embraer SA (EMBR3)  (EMBR3 BS) rose 0.8 percent to 13.43 reais. The
aircraft manufacturer said in an e-mailed statement after the
market closed yesterday that it signed an agreement with
 Aviation Industry Corp. (600316)  of  China  to build the Legacy 600/650
executive jets in China.  Vigor Alimentos SA (VIGR3)  (VIGR3 BS), the Brazilian dairy products
maker that  JBS SA (JBSS3)  spun off in a share swap yesterday, fell 20
percent on its first day of trading in Sao Paulo to 6.40 reais,
down from an offering price of 7.96 reais.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Denyse Godoy in Sao Paulo at 
 dgodoy2@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
